data.enText: a delicate material made from threads of cotton, silk, etc. that are twisted into a pattern of holes

data.chText: 由带子系紧；把…用带子系牢
data.enText: to be fastened with laces ; to fasten sth with laces

data.chText: 她穿着一件在侧面系带子的连衣裙。
data.enText: She was wearing a dress that laced up at the side.
He was sitting on the bed lacing up his shoes.
to put a lace through the holes in a shoe, a boot, etc.

data.chText: 给（饮料等）掺（少量的酒、药、毒药等）
data.enText: to add a small amount of alcohol, a drug, poison, etc. to a drink

data.chText: 他在她的牛奶里加了少量朗姆酒。
data.enText: He had laced her milk with rum.
to add a particular quality to a book, speech, etc.

data.chText: 她的谈话因有趣的题外话而增色。
data.enText: Her conversation was laced with witty asides.

data.chText: 使编织（或交织、缠绕）在一起
data.enText: to twist sth together with another thing

data.chText: 他们手指交叉着坐在那里。
data.enText: They sat with their fingers laced.

means: 给(饮料等)掺(少量的酒、药、毒药等)
使编织（或交织、缠绕）在一起

trans: 用系带束紧；用鞋带系（鞋）

tr: a delicate decorative fabric woven in an open web of symmetrical patterns
a cord that is drawn through eyelets or around hooks in order to draw together two edges (as of a shoe or garment)

example: Twine the threads into a rope
The Flemish women were lacing in front of the cathedral

value.def: Lace is a very delicate cloth which is made with a lot of holes in it. It is made by twisting together very fine threads of cotton to form patterns.

example.ex: She finally found the perfect gown, a beautiful creation trimmed with lace.
example.tran: 她终于找到了理想的礼服——一袭饰有蕾丝的美丽长裙。

value.def: Laces are thin pieces of material that are put through special holes in some types of clothing, especially shoes. The laces are tied together in order to tighten the clothing.

example.ex: Barry was sitting on the bed, tying the laces of an old pair of running shoes.
example.tran: 巴里正坐在床上系他那双旧跑鞋的鞋带。

value.def: If you lace something such as a pair of shoes, you tighten the shoes by pulling the laces through the holes, and usually tying them together.

example.ex: I have a good pair of skates, but no matter how tightly I lace them, my ankles wobble.
example.tran: 我有一双不错的溜冰鞋，可是不管我把鞋带系得多紧，脚脖子那里还是空落落的。

example.ex: He sat on the steps, and laced up his boots...
example.tran: 他坐在台阶上系靴子的鞋带。

example.ex: Nancy was lacing her shoe up when the doorbell rang.
example.tran: 门铃响时南希正在系鞋带。

value.tran: 用系带束紧;用鞋带系（鞋）

value.def: To lace food or drink with a substance such as alcohol or a drug means to put a small amount of the substance into the food or drink.

example.ex: She laced his food with sleeping pills.
example.tran: 她在他的食物里掺了安眠药。

value.tran: 在（饮料或食物）里掺入（少量的酒、药等）

value.def: If you lace your speech or writing with words of a particular kind, you include a lot of those words in what you say or write.

example.ex: Fred liked to lace his conversation with military terms.
example.tran: 弗雷德喜欢在谈话中时不时蹦几个军事术语。

value.tran: 在（言谈或文章）里夹杂（某种话语）

value.def: If you lace your fingers together, you put the palms of your hands together and fold your fingers over, fitting the fingers of one hand between the fingers of the other.

example.ex: He took to lacing his fingers together in an attempt to keep his hands still.
example.tran: 为了不让双手发颤，他十指紧扣。
